  "http://www.oasis-open.org/docbook/xml/4.2/docbookx.dtd"--><ns3215:section xmlns:ns3215="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xml:id="resources.information.technologies.java.j2ee.introduction.j2eeApis.jaxb">

  <ns3216:title xmlns:ns3216="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">The Java Architecture for XML Binding (JAXB)</ns3216:title>
  <ns3217:para xmlns:ns3217="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
    JAXB, the <ns3218:emphasis xmlns:ns3218="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Java Architecture for XML Binding</ns3218:emphasis>
    implements a natural mapping layer between Java classes and XML schemas.
    This means the object state can seamlessly be transferred between
    a Java Object (instance) and and XML instance document. This is done in
    a very natural mechanism using Java annotations.
  </ns3217:para>
  <ns3219:para xmlns:ns3219="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
    JAXB is often used in conjunction with JAX-WS, where it performs 
    marshalling and de-marshalling of SOAP messages onto Java objects during 
    service requests.
  </ns3219:para>
